  "prompt": "Where do we get beef jerky or biltong in London?",
  "response": "In London, there are several places where you can find beef jerky and biltong. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Specialty Stores**: Look for specialty food shops or butcher shops that focus on cured meats. They often carry a selection of jerky and biltong.\n\n2. **Online Retailers**: Websites like Amazon or dedicated jerky and biltong companies such as **Biltong Box** and **Jerky.com** offer online ordering with delivery options.\n\n3. **Markets**: Borough Market and Camden Market might have stalls that sell artisanal jerky and biltong.\n\n4. **Health Food Stores**: Shops like Holland & Barrett often stock jerky, and you might find biltong in some health-oriented stores.\n\n5. **Supermarkets**: Major supermarkets like Tesco, Sainsbury\u2019s, and Waitrose occasionally have beef jerky in their snack aisles. Biltong might also be available in some larger stores.\n\n6. **Ethnic Grocery Stores**: South African shops and other specialty ethnic grocery stores might have biltong, given its popularity in South Africa.\n\n7. **Pop-Up Shops**: Occasionally, food festivals or pop-up events in London feature vendors who sell jerky and biltong.\n\nAlways check the specific store\u2019s availability, as products may vary.",
